<h2 class="pen"><a rel="bookmark" https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=1057" title="Permanent link to this article">Unshelved</a></h2>

<div class="post">

<div class="entrytext">

	<p>Darlene had ordered me the latest collection of Unshelved comic strips for my birthday, but it didn&#8217;t show up.</p>

	<p>So she emailed Bill Barnes (half of the team that creates the daily strip) and asked about the delivery. He wrote back that the payment hadn&#8217;t been received and that it&#8217;ll ship when it&#8217;s received.</p>

	<p>Then a little later he wrote back, apologizing profusely. The envelope ended up with his personal mail instead of the business mail and (like all of us) hadn&#8217;t gone through it.</p>

	<p>Today he sent another email that the book was in the mail and that for goofing they tossed in a free baseball cap! Darlene was just glad to hear the check didn&#8217;t get lost and they kick in a free gift.</p>

	<p>Library folks are classy folks, it just goes to show.</p>

	<p>Send the guys a little love and subscribe to the comic strip, put a link on your website and/or buy some of the fun stuff they have in their store (I have a library raid t-shirt). If you work in a library or love libraries, it&#8217;s a fun read.</p>

	<p><a title="Overdue Media, home of Unshelved - a comic strip about a library" href="http://www.unshelved.com/">Unshelved: a comic strip about a library.</a></p>



 

<p class="postmetadata alt">

<small>This entry was posted on Feb 16 by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a>. You can skip to the end and leave a response using the comment form.</small></p>

</div>

</div>




	

